4. Write a Ruby program which accepts the radius of a circle from the user
 and compute the parameter and area.

 pi = 3.14
 r = gets.chop
 def parameter
   @parameter = 2 * pi * r
   print( "The parameter is #{parameter}" )
 end
 def area
   @area = pi * r ** 2
   print( "The area is #{area}" )
 end
